challengeName: CSFV Social Network Sharing Header Update
detailedRequirements:
Task Overview

The goal of this challenge is to improve the social sharing header.

Task Requirements

  • This task will update 6 websites :
    • main site : github repository is csfv_frontend_module
    • minisite1 : github repository is csfv_minisite_frontend_module branch minisite1
    • minisite2 : github repository is csfv_minisite_frontend_module branch minisite2
    • minisite3 : github repository is csfv_minisite_frontend_module branch minisite3
    • minisite4 : github repository is csfv_minisite_frontend_module branch minisite4
    • minisite5 : github repository is csfv_minisite_frontend_module branch minisite5
  • Update social sharing header to open on 'hover' instead of opening on 'click', and to close when 'hover' out. (note that as long as the user is moving the mouse horizontally between the social icons the panel should remain opened, and when user navigate to the sharing expanded div panel it should be considered as hover on as well, we trigger hover out only when user move out of the social icons area and the expanded panels area), so you need to properly assign the div that should handle the hover on/out or set a timeout)
  • In minisite4, update the title of panels from white to text color used in the theme
  • In all websites fix the like button position and fix loading facebook users div as it suppose to load users who liked FB page (same as we are doing to twitter followers panel).
  • Link the 4 icons headers to the social network pages, same as we are doing in footer, the href values will come from configuration.

 

Github Code

CSFV websites code exists in private github repository http://github.com/topcoderinc

Here is the repositories (you can search for them in the github.com link provided above) :

  • csfv_frontend_module (this is the main site)
  • csfv_minisite_frontend_module (we have 5 minisites, use branches : minisite1, minisite2, minisite3, minisite4, and minisite5)

Deliverables

  • Patch file of changes.
  • Text file with any note to reviewer.
